          <para id="id1168071289932"> If product A generates a profit of $60 per unit and product B a profit of $50 per unit, how many units of each product should be manufactured to maximize profit, and what is the maximum profit?</para>
        </problem>
        <solution id="oo-id1168073615120">
          <para id="id1168071511231">(35, 100); $2600</para>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
      
      <exercise id="id1168072113908">
        <problem id="oo-id1168075850084">
          <para id="id1168074561820">A company produces three types of shoes, formal, casual, and athletic, at its two factories, Factory I and Factory II. Daily production of each factory for each type of shoe is listed below. </para>
       
      <table id="id1168075989422" summary="A 4x3 table showing the daily production of three types of shoes at two different factories.">
